summary: Neutron edges closer to launch as RKLB completes testing of its reusable Hungry Hippo fairing and ships hardware to Virginia.

headline: EVIO Launches Hybrid-Electric Aircraft Program with 450 Pre-Orders
summary: MONTREAL, December 11, 2025--EVIO, Inc. makes its public debut with 450 preorders for its EVIO 810 hybrid-electric regional aircraft, expected to enter service by the early 2030s.

headline: Elon Musk Appears to Confirm SpaceX IPO. Here’s What Could Happen Next.
summary: Elon Musk appears to have confirmed IPO plans for his rocket company SpaceX—and revealed why it might happen soon.  On Wednesday evening, Musk responded to a tweet from Ars Technica senior space editor Eric Berger, who posted a story about the reasons SpaceX, which has seemingly been content to stay private, without a need for more capital, might pursue an initial public offering of stock.  “As usual, Eric is accurate,” said Musk.

headline: BAE Systems Clinches $1.7B APKWS Production Contract From US Navy
summary: BAESY lands a $1.7B Navy contract to ramp up APKWS kit production, meeting surging U.S. and international demand for precision munitions.
